The paper deals with video classification using deep learning techniques, specifically ResNet and Inception V3 architectures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper incorporates audio information, which could potentially fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of deep models and ensemble techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper involves feature extraction and aggregation, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with temporal segmentation, which could potentially fall under the software engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
